docblock.description: Writes $bytes to the end of the stream.
docblock.long-description:
Writing may not happen immediately if the stream chooses to buffer. If you want to write these bytes with immediate effect, call \commit() after calling write().
This method returns the sequence ID of the write (i.e. 1 for first, 2 for second, etc etc).

docblock.description: For any bytes that are currently buffered inside the stream, force them off the buffer.

docblock.long-description: The stream acts as an observer, receiving all data that is written. All \write() and \flushBuffers() operations will be mirrored.
